ADDIS ABABA, Ethiopia, April 2, 2019/APO Group/ --
                                                        
                            Frédéric Bontems, French Ambassador in Ethiopia and to the African Union, and Panos Navrozidis, Action Against Hunger Ethiopia country director, signed a funding support contract this morning for an emergency cash response for conflict internally displaced people in West Wollega zone of Oromia region.



This project, funded within the framework of the French food aid program, aims at improving the response to the needs of internally displaced people in West Wollega zone, following inter-communal violence in Benishangul-Gumuz region.